{"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/Se","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SE","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SQ","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SH","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat"],"generated":true,"title":"Enumeration Cases","anchor":"Enumeration-Cases"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/init(from:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/serialized"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/Equatable-Implementations"],"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each mode maps to a specific "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Virtualization.framework"},{"type":"text","text":" network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device attachment type. The mode determines how the guest’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"network traffic is routed relative to the host and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"external network."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Choosing a Network Mode","anchor":"Choosing-a-Network-Mode","level":2},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mode"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Guest → Internet"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Host → Guest"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Entitlement"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✓"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Via resolved IP"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✓"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Own LAN IP"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"com.apple.vm.networking","type":"codeVoice"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✗"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✗"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For host-guest communication without full network access,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" mode and communicate via the VirtIO socket"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZVirtioSocketDeviceConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"), which is always"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attached regardless of network mode."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bridged mode requires the "},{"code":"com.apple.vm.networking","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"restricted entitlement, which must be requested from Apple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Developer Technical Support."}]}],"style":"note"},{"type":"heading","text":"Why There Is No Host-Only Mode","anchor":"Why-There-Is-No-Host-Only-Mode","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework provides three network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attachment types: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZNATNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZBridgedNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":". None of these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implements host-only semantics directly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A host-only mode would require a user-space virtual network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"switch built on top of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handling raw Ethernet frames, DHCP, and packet routing — a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"substantial subsystem that would need its own lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"management and security hardening. Rather than ship a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"half-baked implementation or silently fall back to NAT"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which would give VMs unintended internet access), this enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only exposes modes that the Virtualization framework supports"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"natively."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need isolated host-guest communication, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the VirtIO socket device. If you need full IP networking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between VMs, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on a dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host-only network interface."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit11NetworkModeO","title":"NetworkMode","symbolKind":"enum","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The network configuration mode for a virtual machine."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"kind":"symbol","